===Noun===
{{en-noun|galaxies}}

# {{context|now|_|rare}} The [[Milky Way]]; the apparent band of concentrated stars which appears in the night sky over earth. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
#* '''1633''', John Donne, "Sapho to Philænis":
#*: So may thy cheekes red outweare scarlet dye, / And their white, whitenesse of the '''''Galaxie''''' [...].
# {{context|galaxy}} Any of the collections of many millions of stars, [[galactic]] dust, [[black hole]]s, etc. existing as independent and coherent [[system]]s, of which there are billions in the known [[universe]]. {{defdate|from 19th c.}}

